{
  "texts": [
    "53)53From the formal power series expansion of the indices, we find that the half-indices (3.48) and (3.52) give rise to the same result!",
    "So the half-indices (3.49) and (3.53) are equivalent.",
    "This implies the duality of the interfaces involving the disconnected O(2N) gauge group O(2N)|USp(2N) NS5-type interface ⇔ O(2N)|SO(2N + 1) D5 ′ -type interface.",
    "61)61Note that the expressions (3.60) and (3.61) become (3.50) and (3.52) when N = M respectively.",
    "It turns out that the half-index (3.55) for the NS5 ′ -type SO(2N)|USp(2M) interface excellently matches with the half-index (3.58) for N > M and the half-index (3.60) for N < M!"
  ]
}